{"title_page": "Vico Sotto", "text_new": "{{Like resume|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Filipino politician}}\n{{Philippine name|Nubla|Sotto}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Vico Sotto\n| image               = Vico Sotto at UA&P CRC meet with Pasig students on June 6 2019.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| caption             = Sotto on October 2019\n| office              = Mayor of [[Pasig]]\n| 1blankname          = Vice Mayor\n| 1namedata           = Iyo Christian C. Bernardo\n| term_start          = June 30, 2019\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = Robert \"Bobby\" Eusebio\n| office1             = Member of the [[Sangguniang Panlungsod]] of [[Pasig]] from the First District\n| term_start1         = June 30, 2016\n| term_end1           = June 30, 2019\n| office2             = Chairman of Public Relations and Information Committee<br />[[Sangguniang Panlungsod]] of [[Pasig]]\n| term_start2         = June 30, 2016\n| term_end2           = June 30, 2019\n| birth_name          = Victor Mar\u00eda Regis Nubla Sotto\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1989|06|17}}\n| birth_place         = [[Pasig]], [[Metro Manila]], Philippines\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = [[Aksyon Demokratiko]]\n| otherparty          = \n| mother              = [[Coney Reyes]]\n| father              = [[Vic Sotto]]\n| spouse              = \n| relations           = [[Oyo Boy Sotto]] <small>(half-brother)</small><br>[[Tito Sotto]] <small>(uncle)</small><br>[[Vicente Sotto]] <small>(great-grandfather)</small><br>[[Pauleen Luna]] <small>(stepmother)</small><br>[[Gian Sotto]] <small>(cousin)</small>\n| profession          = \n| salary              = \n| portfolio           = \n| partner             = \n| children            = \n| alma_mater          = [[Ateneo de Manila University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|AB]], [[Master of Public Administration|MPA]])\n| website             = \n}}\n'''Victor Mar\u00eda Regis''' \"'''Vico'''\" '''Nubla Sotto''' (born June 17, 1989) is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] politician who is the incumbent Mayor of [[Pasig]], Philippines.<ref name=\"millenialmayor\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1135669/millennial-vico-sotto-takes-oath-as-pasig-city-mayor |title=Millennial Vico Sotto takes oath as Pasig City mayor |last=Mercado |first=Neil Arwin |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=July 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701064708/https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1135669/millennial-vico-sotto-takes-oath-as-pasig-city-mayor |archive-date=July 1, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref> Sotto first entered politics when he ran for a seat on the Pasig City Council in 2016. He won the election as an independent, and served a term in the city council.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/04/22/19/vico-sotto |title=Will Vico Sotto be Pasig's final answer? |last=Carpio |first=Audrey |work=ABS CBN News and Public Affairs |access-date=June 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422101627/https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/04/22/19/vico-sotto |archive-date=April 22, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>  He joined the [[Aksyon Demokratiko]] party and ran for Mayor of Pasig in 2019, taking up a platform of [[Participatory democracy|public consultation]], [[Data-driven decision-making|data-driven governance]], [[universal health care]] in Pasig, prioritizing housing programs, easier access to education, and cracking down on [[Corruption in the Philippines|corruption]].<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/> He won the [[2019 Pasig local elections|2019 election]] to earn a six-year mayoral term.<ref name=\"Lalu\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1075306/aksyon-demokratiko-endorses-5-senatorial-bets |title=Aksyon Demokratiko endorses 9 senatorial bets |last=Lalu |first=Gabriel Pabico |access-date=July 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204032445/https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1075306/aksyon-demokratiko-endorses-5-senatorial-bets |archive-date=February 4, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref> \n\nIn March 2020, he received significant public attention<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\">{{Cite news |last=Malasig |first=Jeline |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/03/18/164558/vico-sotto-has-been-stellar-with-his-proactive-covid-19-initiatives-and-filipinos-want-him-to-lead-the-whole-country/ |title=Vico Sotto has been stellar with his proactive COVID-19 initiatives, and Filipinos want him to lead the whole country |date=March 18, 2020 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\"JCRight\"/> due to his leadership of Pasig's quick, data-driven responses to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Metro Manila]], and the resulting [[2020 Luzon enhanced community quarantine]].<ref name=\"JelouEmpathy\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\">{{Cite news |last=Abellon |first=Bam |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/03/20/20/heres-everything-that-mayor-vico-sotto-has-done-so-far-in-response-to-covid-19 |title=Here\u2019s everything that Mayor Vico Sotto has done so far in response to COVID-19 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320204156/https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/03/20/20/heres-everything-that-mayor-vico-sotto-has-done-so-far-in-response-to-covid-19 |archive-date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nSotto was born on June 17, 1989 to actor-comedian-host [[Vic Sotto]] and actress [[Coney Reyes]].<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>  As the son of two celebrities strongly associated with the noontime variety show ''[[Eat Bulaga!]]'', the public expected that Sotto would make regular appearances on the show. However, he was a shy child who often refused to go onstage; eventually his parents stopped asking him.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/> Sotto attended [[Brent International School]] for most of his grade school and high school.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Libarios |first1=Gabby |title=Vico Sotto: The son also rises |url=https://www.pep.ph/peptionary/146255/vico-sotto-a1294-20190929-lfrm3 |website=Philippine Entertainment Portal |accessdate=March 26, 2020 |date=September 29, 2019}}</ref> He graduated from the [[Ateneo de Manila University]] in 2011 with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree in [[political science]]. Sotto would eventually pursue a career in politics, furthering his mastery by pursuing a post-graduate degree in [[public administration]] at the [[Ateneo School of Government]], where he graduated in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sabillo |first1=Kristine |title=Change in Pasig: How Vico Sotto toppled a dynasty |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/05/22/19/change-in-pasig-how-vico-sotto-toppled-a-dynasty |accessdate=May 22, 2019 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Pasig City Council ==\nSotto became a member of [[Sangguniang Panlungsod]] (City Council) of Pasig in 2016,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/breaking-news/2018/07/10/130366/i-am-not-your-father-pasig-city-councilor-vico-sotto-clarifies-dad-tag-of-newspaper/ |title='I am not your father': Pasig City councilor Vico Sotto clarifies 'dad' tag of newspaper - Interaksyon |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |date=October 15, 2018 |work=interaksyon.com |access-date=July 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181015072016/http://www.interaksyon.com/breaking-news/2018/07/10/130366/i-am-not-your-father-pasig-city-councilor-vico-sotto-clarifies-dad-tag-of-newspaper/ |archive-date=October 15, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> serving a single term<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/> which ended when he was sworn in as Mayor on June 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web \n|url= https://www.pep.ph/news/107205/strongpep-special-reportstrong-how-did-showbiz-clans-fare-in-eleksyon2016\n|title= PEP SPECIAL REPORT. How did showbiz clans fare in #Eleksyon2016?\n|last1=\n|first1= \n|date= May 11, 2016\n|publisher= [[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]\n|access-date= May 18, 2019\n}}</ref> \n\nAs an independent Councilor, Sotto faced stiff opposition to his initiatives, making it difficult for him to introduce legislation.  As a result, he was forced to strategize, sacrificing some of the measures{{which|date=April 2020}} he wanted to pass in favor of those he thought most important{{which|date=April 2020}}.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/>\n\nHe focused his attention on the \u201cThe Pasig Transparency Mechanism Ordinance,\u201d which seeks the disclosure of public records, including financial documents and contracts, upon request by ordinary citizens.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/> Upon its passage, it became the first-ever localized version of the [[Freedom of Information Order (Philippines)|freedom of information law]] in [[Metro Manila]].<ref>{{cite web \n|url= https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1040986/pasig-passes-own-version-of-foi-bill\n|title= Pasig passes own version of FOI bill\n|last1= Enano\n|first1= Jhesset\n|date= October 10, 2018\n|publisher= [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]\n|access-date= May 18, 2019\n}}</ref>\n\n== Pasig Mayor ==\n[[File:Vico_Sotto_at_UA&P_CRC_meet_with_Pasig_students_on_June_6_2019.jpg|thumb|right|Mayor Vico Sotto speaking before Pasig City High School students at the [[University of Asia and the Pacific]], June 6, 2019]]\n{{Recentism|section=yes|date=April 2020}}\n\n=== 2019 campaign ===\nWhen Sotto ran for Mayor in Pasig in 2019, he campaigned on a platform that he called his \u201cBig V\u201d (Big Five) Agenda, saying he planned to focus on universal healthcare, housing programs, education, public consultation, and anti-corruption efforts.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.philstar.com/nation/2019/05/06/1915546/ibanaman-vs-continuity-political-payanig-pasig |title=#IbaNaman vs continuity: Political 'payanig' in Pasig |last=Cabico |first=Gaea Katreena |date=May 6, 2019 |work=The [[Philippine Star]] |access-date=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== 2019 campaign platform ====\n===== Universal health care in Pasig =====\nDuring the campaign, Sotto indicated that his top priority would be healthcare in Pasig, citing it as an important anti-poverty measure. He noted that while there were numerous health facilities such as hospitals in Pasig, it was important that they be properly supplied with medicine.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>\n\n===== Housing programs =====\nAnother priority area Sotto said he would prioritize was housing.  He said he would try to make sure that every family living in Pasig would eventually own their own house.  He also promised that informal settlers would not be forced to leave their homes until primary services and livelihood could be assured at the selected relocation site.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>\n\n===== Education =====\nAs part of his Platform on Education, Sotto pledged to make it easier and cheaper for Pasig residents to qualify for scholarships, removing barriers and reducing requirements in the application process. Among the requirements he singled out for removal was the requirement that parents submit copies of their voter's registration documents while applying for Pasig City scholarships. <ref name=\"metromanila.politics.com.ph\">{{cite web |url=https://metromanila.politics.com.ph/2019/04/14/vico-sotto-wants-to-simplify-scholarship-for-pasig-students-no-more-extra-fees/ |title=Vico Sotto wants to simplify scholarship for Pasig students: No more extra fees! |date=April 14, 2019 |website=Politiko Metro Manila |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417143338/https://metromanila.politics.com.ph/2019/04/14/vico-sotto-wants-to-simplify-scholarship-for-pasig-students-no-more-extra-fees/ |archive-date=April 17, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=July 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Public consultation =====\nIn response to the management style of the previous administration Sotto also promised during the campaign that all city government decisions would go through a public consultation process.  He also promised transparency in government projects, from planning to implementation to monitoring and evaluation.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/> More specific initiatives proposed by Sotto under this agenda item include public officials from appointing members on local special bodies, and forming sectoral councils in areas such as like transport and environmental protection, tasked with developing legislation in those areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1119590/sottos-pledge-i-wont-do-a-eusebio |title=Sotto's pledge: I won't do a Eusebio &#124; Inquirer News |publisher=|date=May 16, 2019 |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Anti-corruption drive =====\nSotto also indicated that his administration's anti-corruption drive would begin with the establishment of a \"Government Efficiency and Anti-Corruption Commission,\" the putting up a Pasig City anti-corruption hotline, and ensuring that a Non-Government Organization or Civil Society Organization would watch over each of the City Government's bidding processes.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>\n\n==== Data-driven governance ====\n{{see also|Data-driven decision-making}}\nA key strategy Sotto said he would use in order to achieve his five-point campaign platform was that of [[Data-driven decision-making|data-driven governance]]. On the campaign trail, he said that one of the roots of poor public service in Pasig was the culture of \"palakasan,\" where citizens have to curry the favor of officials in order to get services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/06/30/q-a-with-metro-manila-mayors/ |title=Q & A with Metro Manila mayors: \u00bb Manila Bulletin News |publisher=News.mb.com.ph |date= |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref>  Sotto's proposed solution to this problem was to make sure that decisions on the provision and prioritization of services would be based on data, rather than the political will or whims of officials.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://opinion.inquirer.net/121636/finding-vico |title=Finding Vico &#124; Inquirer Opinion |publisher=Opinion.inquirer.net |date= |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://business.inquirer.net/274577/transforming-metro-manila-cities |title=Transforming Metro Manila cities &#124; Inquirer Business |publisher=|date= |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019 electoral victory ===\nVico Sotto defeated incumbent mayor Robert Eusebio in the [[2019 Pasig local elections]], ending the 27-year rule of the Eusebio family over the Pasig City Mayoralty.<ref name=\"millenialmayor\"/> He was sworn into office on June 30, 2019.<ref name=\"Rachelle\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.pep.ph/news/144282/pasi-mayor-vico-sotto-funniest-tweets-a716-20190701 |title=Vico Sotto has the funniest tweets after winning as Pasig mayor |last=Siazon |first=Rachelle |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703093135/https://www.pep.ph/news/144282/pasi-mayor-vico-sotto-funniest-tweets-a716-20190701 |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live |publisher=pep.ph}}</ref>\n\n=== Early policies and positions ===\n==== Policy against politicking ====\nSotto received favorable press coverage<ref name=\"tarpaulinABS\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/06/20/19/netizens-laud-vico-sottos-plea-to-have-his-tarpaulin-removed |title=Netizens laud Vico Sotto's plea to have his tarpaulin removed |last=News |first=ABS-CBN |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620092917/https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/06/20/19/netizens-laud-vico-sottos-plea-to-have-his-tarpaulin-removed |archive-date=June 20, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> when he issued a policy statement against the proliferation of political propaganda signages, even before his inauguration.  A supporter had taken the occasion of Sotto's 30th Birthday on July 17 to post a tarpaulin greeting the Mayor-elect on his birthday.  A few days later, Sotto went on Twitter to request that the tarpaulin be removed, and asserting that such politically-oriented signage bearing his image would be discouraged during his term.<ref name=\"InteraksyonTarpaulin\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/06/21/150819/vico-sotto-first-instructions-mayor/ |title=Pasig Mayor-elect Vico Sotto's first instructions before assuming office |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |date=June 21, 2019 |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622150721/http://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/06/21/150819/vico-sotto-first-instructions-mayor/ |archive-date=June 22, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nHe has also made statements discouraging the \"celebrity treatment\" of politicians in the Philippines\n<ref>{{Cite news |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/trends-spotlights/2019/08/26/153962/pasig-city-mayor-vico-sotto-tells-public-stop-viewing-government-officials-celebrities/ |title=Pasig Mayor Vico Sotto wants the public to stop treating government officials as celebrities |date=August 26, 2019 |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828031111/http://www.interaksyon.com/trends-spotlights/2019/08/26/153962/pasig-city-mayor-vico-sotto-tells-public-stop-viewing-government-officials-celebrities/ |archive-date=August 28, 2019 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==== Reassessment of traffic management ====\nSotto's first executive order upon being sworn in as Mayor put in place a Pasig City Traffic Management Task Force, which was tasked to \"review and propose new solutions for the current mobility and traffic situation\" within 45 days.<ref name=\"Drei\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/mayor-vico-sotto-pasig-coding-a962-20190701 |title=Mayor Vico Sotto's first executive order suspends odd-even coding |last=Laurel |first=Drei |work=Top Gear Magazine |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703093727/https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/mayor-vico-sotto-pasig-coding-a962-20190701 |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref>  The same executive order abolished the Pasig City odd-even coding scheme which the previous administration had implemented on top of the [[Metro Manila Development Authority]]'s [[Unified Vehicular Volume Reduction Program|Traffic Coding Scheme]] - a double burden which Sotto had earlier decried as being \"disjointed and unjust.\"<ref name=\"Drei\"/>\n\n==== Zagu Foods picketline incident ====\nOn July 9, 2019, media reports noted that Sotto had visited protesters who were being forced away from their picket line in front of the main factory of Zagu Foods Corporation in Pasig.  He reminded Zagu Foods' management that the protesters were within their rights to engage in protest activities.<ref name=\"Consuelo\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1139740/vico-sotto-to-zagu-management-respect-workers-right-to-picket |title=Vico Sotto to Zagu management: Respect workers' right to picket |last=Marquez |first=Consuelo |date=July 9, 2019 |work=The [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=July 10, 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"CatalinaRicciRegencyZagu\">{{Cite news |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/11/18/157591/pasig-mayor-vico-sotto-took-side-constituents-against-companies-twice/ |title=The two instances when Pasig Mayor Vico Sotto took the side of his constituents against big companies |date=November 18, 2019 |work=interaksyon |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119130202/http://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/11/18/157591/pasig-mayor-vico-sotto-took-side-constituents-against-companies-twice/ |archive-date=November 19, 2019 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==== Regent Foods picketline incident ====\nIn November 2019, Sotto intervened in another picketline incident - this time with Regent Foods Corporation, 23 of whose workers were arrested after they clashed with company security guards and police officers while protesting the company's labor practices.  Sotto called on Regency to \"rethink on the charges it filed against its employees,\" issuing a statement saying that \u201cThese people are not criminals; they do not have the goal of hurting you. They are fighting for what they believe to be just.\u201d  Sotto also said he was raising funds for the bail money which the 23 arrested employees would need.<ref name=\"CatalinaRicciRegencyZagu\"/>\n\n==== Crackdown on illegal POGO-related services ====\nIn February 2020, Sotto again gained positive media reactions as a result of his efforts to crack down on illegally-operating businesses linked to Philippine Offshore Gaming Operators (POGOs).  On February 23, Sotto ordered the closure Fu Yuan Ji, a restaurant catering to POGO employees which had opened without getting a permit to operate from the city.<ref name=\"CatalinaRicciPOGOs\">{{Cite news |last=Malasig |first=Jeline |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/02/24/162814/vico-sotto-pasig-city-crackdown-pogos-chinese-restaurant/ |title=Vico Sotto gives teeth to city laws vs unregistered Chinese resto |date=February 24, 2020 |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225074628/https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/02/24/162814/vico-sotto-pasig-city-crackdown-pogos-chinese-restaurant/ |archive-date=February 25, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== COVID-19 crisis response ===\nSotto received significant positive attention in both traditional and social media in response to Pasig's quick, data-driven responses to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Metro Manila]], and the resulting [[2020 Luzon enhanced community quarantine]] beginnning March 17, 2020.<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"JCRight\">{{Cite news |last=Gotinga |first=J. C. |url=http://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/inside-track/255321-vico-sotto-says-always-do-what-believe-is-right |title=Vico Sotto: I will always just do what I believe is right |date=March 21, 2020 |work=[[Rappler]] |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321162851/https://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/inside-track/255321-vico-sotto-says-always-do-what-believe-is-right |archive-date=March 21, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"JelouEmpathy\">{{Cite magazine |last=Galang |first=Jelou |date=March 20, 2020 |title=Empathy with action is Mayor Vico Sotto's winning combo |url=https://www.scoutmag.ph/featured/empathy-with-action-mayor-vico-sotto-jeloug-20200320 |url-status=live |magazine=Scout Magazine |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163418/https://www.scoutmag.ph/featured/empathy-with-action-mayor-vico-sotto-jeloug-20200320 |archive-date=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Before the Luzon quarantine ====\nNational media outlets<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"JCRight\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\"/> noted that even before the national government implemented a community quarantine in the Metro Manila area, Sotto\u2019s administration prepared for the coming of COVID-19 by:\n* asking experts to brief Pasig\u2019s health workers about COVID-19 cases;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* establishing and training COVID-19 response teams;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* Providing a total of more than 1,000 sets of disinfecting kits to all of the Pasig\u2019s barangays;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/> and\n* Disinfecting public places \u2013 from the public market and public schools to even streets and sidewalks, as well as Pasig City Hall.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* Sotto himself spoke with the management with Pasig city\u2019s private hospitals to make sure they are ready to take on COVID-19 patients.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* Sotto also kept Pasig constituents constantly informed about necessary precautions and updated about the situation through his official social media accounts.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n\n==== During the Luzon quarantine ====\nAccounts<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"JCRight\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\"/> also noted that once the enhanced quarantine was put in place on March 17, the Sotto administration:\n* Placed the city government on skeleton staff, in keeping with national policy, rearranging schedules so frontline government services could be sustained;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* ensured the full salaries for all city government employees;<ref name=\"ABSCBNPasigSalariesCOVID\">{{Cite news |last=News |first=ABS-CBN |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/18/20/all-pasig-employees-to-get-full-pay-during-covid-19-quarantine-vico-sotto |title=All Pasig employees to get full pay during COVID-19 quarantine: Vico Sotto |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Gotinga |first=J. C. |url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/254893-vico-sotto-vows-full-salaries-pasig-government-workers-coronavirus-lockdown |title=Vico Sotto vows full salaries for all Pasig government workers during lockdown |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* implemented a nightly 8 pm to 5 am curfew;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* put up rules penalizing hoarders of essential goods;<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/> \n* continued disinfecting operations in public places,<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/> and procured disinfectant drones so that hard-to-reach areas could be disinfected;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/vico-sotto-disinfectant-drones-src-esquireph-a4349-20200318 |title=Pasig City procures disinfectant drones to fight COVID-19 |work=Top Gear Philippines |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"ABSCBNDronesMotelsCOVID\"/>\n* established sanitation tents at the Pasig city hall, Pasig City General Hospital (PCGH), and the Pasig City Children\u2019s Hospital (Child\u2019s Hope);<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"SanitationTentsLook\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/18/20/look-sanitation-tents-installed-in-pasig-city-hall-public-hospitals |title=LOOK: Sanitation tents installed in Pasig City hall, public hospitals |work=ABS CBN News and Public Affairs |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* distributed food packs and bottles of vitamins to Pasig residents;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/> and \n* arranged for the conversion of some of Pasig\u2019s motels as quarantine facilities COVID-19 patients.<ref name=\"ABSCBNDronesMotelsCOVID\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/19/20/pasig-buys-disinfection-drones-turns-motels-to-quarantine-and-staff-lodging-vico-sotto |title=Pasig buys disinfection drones, turns motels to quarantine and staff lodging: Vico Sotto |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* Sotto himself regularly inspected the checkpoints to make sure procedures were being followed and the rights of citizens respected despite the curfew.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\"/>\n* Sotto also met the appropriate teams from The Medical City, PCGH, Child\u2019s Hope, and the City Health Office, ensuring proper coordination and the exchange of good practices in pandemic response.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n\n==== Transportation initiatives during the Luzon quarantine ====\nSotto's administration also executed a number of transportation initiatives during the enhanced community quarantine.  Most of these were generally praised, including the deployment of Pasig city\u2019s fleet of buses to service essential workers, and the lending of \u201cPasig Bike Share\u201d bicycle units to health workers and other frontline personnel.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n\nOne initiative that was questioned during the early days of the quarantine, however, was that Pasig initially allowed limited tricycle trips for people with legitimate reasons to commute, such as chemotherapy and other health issues.<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/>  This was done on the basis of Pasig city risk analysis which determined that more residents would die if they were deprived of transport services.<ref name=\"AllysaRisk\">{{Cite news |last=Nievera |first=Allysa |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/18/mayor-sotto-says-total-ban-on-tricycles-in-pasig-adds-risk-to-health-situation/ |title=Mayor Sotto says total ban on tricycles in Pasig adds risk to health situation  |date=March 18, 2020}}</ref>  Sotto thus went on national media pleading to the national governement that an exception be made for Pasig's tricycles, based on the studies.<ref name=\"JCUrge\">{{Cite news |last=Gotinga |first=J. C. |url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/254986-vico-sotto-urges-national-government-allow-tricycles-coronavirus-lockdown |title=Vico Sotto urges nat'l gov't to allow tricycles during coronavirus lockdown |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> However, on March 19, 2020 the national government informed Sotto that they insisted all forms of public transport, including tricycles, would be banned.  Sotto immediately responded that Pasig would stop allowing Tricycles to ply their routes.<ref name=\"PasigTricycleCompliance\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/metro/730479/vico-sotto-pasig-to-follow-nat-l-gov-t-on-tricycles-ban/story/ |title=Vico Sotto: Pasig to follow nat\u2019l gov\u2019t on tricycles ban |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nIn response to media coverage of this, private companies began donating vehicles such as Community Managed Electric Transport (COMET) bus units to augment Pasig city's fleet of free rides that can be offered to the public.<ref name=\"PasigCOMETs\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.wheninmanila.com/tricycles-not-allowed-pasig-gets-creative-by-deploying-these-electric-vehicles/ |title=Tricycles not allowed, Pasig gets creative by deploying these electric vehicles |date=March 20, 2020 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref>  The city was eventualy able to acquire e-tricycles which were specifically assigned to provide free transportation for Pasig City residents who had health and hospitalization needs such as dialysis or chemotherapy<ref name=\"DreiETrykes\">{{Cite news |last=Laurel |first=Drei |url=https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/pasig-city-free-transport-dialysis-chemotherapy-a962-20200330 |title=Pasig City offers free transport for those in need of dialysis, chemotherapy |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> - the residents which the risk assessment determined would be endangered by the ban on tricycles.<ref name=\"AllysaRisk\"/><ref name=\"VicoUmapela\">{{Cite news |last=Canoy |first=Jeff |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/video/news/03/18/20/vico-sotto-umapelang-payagang-bumiyahe-ang-tricycle-drivers-sa-pasig |title=Vico Sotto umapelang payagang bumiyahe ang tricycle drivers sa Pasig |date=March 18, 2020 |work=ABS CBN News and Public Affairs |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=tl}}</ref>\n\n===== Tricycle operations controversy =====\n\nOn March 24, the Philippine legislature passed the [[Bayanihan to Heal as One Act]] which gave national government additional powers to combat the pandemic.<ref name=\"CatalinaRicciOne\">{{Cite news |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/03/26/164950/bayanihan-to-heal-as-one-act-whats-at-stake-law/ |title=The 'Bayanihan to Heal as One Act' and what's at stake in the law |date=March 26, 2020 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |work=InterAksyon |language=en-US}}</ref> The [[National Bureau of Investigation (Philippines)|National Bureau of Investigation]] (NBI) invoked the said law on April 1 against Sotto, summoning him to appear at their office on April 7, claiming that he had violated the law's provision which bans public transportation. Sotto responded by saying that he had complied with the national government's order to stop tricycle operations [[Ex post facto law|prior to the enactment of the law]] on March 25. Senate President [[Tito Sotto]], an uncle of the mayor and a principal author of the law in question, supported his claim.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/256687-senators-reaction-nbi-summon-vico-sotto-coronavirus-lockdown|title=Tito Sotto 'defends' Vico: 'Violation of Bayanihan law can't be retroactive'|last=Rey|first=Aika|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> Vice President [[Leni Robredo]] and Senator [[Francis Pangilinan]] were among the other politicians who questioned the NBI's actions, stating the unconstitutionality of criminalizing an act committed retroactively.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/4/1/nbi-vico-sotto-luzon-quarantine.html|title=NBI asks Vico Sotto to explain 'violation' of quarantine policy|work=CNN Philippines|language=en|access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> Social media responded heavily with criticism towards the NBI for allegedly singling out the mayor, with the [[hashtag]] \"#ProtectVico\" trended on [[Twitter]] worldwide that day.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vico Sotto 'confident nothing will happen' in NBI probe |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/video/news/04/05/20/vico-sotto-confident-nothing-will-happen-in-nbi-probe |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Political affiliation ==\nSotto originally ran for a seat in the Pasig Sanguniang Panglungsod as an independent, and won a seat without having any party affiliation.  \n\nIn 2019, Sotto was sworn in as a member of [[Aksyon Demokratiko]], a national political party founded by former Senator [[Raul Roco]] in 1997. He was sworn into the party alongside [[Roman Romulo]], who would also win as representative in Pasig City's sole legislative district; and Marielle del Rosario, who likewise ran as representative of [[Navotas City]].<ref name=\"Lalu\"/>  Sotto has refused to join bigger, more-established parties despite political pressure to do so,<ref name=\"MRCJune62019\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1121807/vico-sotto-we-need-to-go-beyond-yellow-vs-dds |title=Vico Sotto: We need to go beyond yellow vs DDS |last=Reysio-Cruz |first=Matthew |date=June 3, 2019 |work=The [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=June 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521224751/https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1121807/vico-sotto-we-need-to-go-beyond-yellow-vs-dds |archive-date=May 21, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref> explaining that he chose to join the party because he shared its platform of pushing for Freedom of Information, political party reform, and the end of political dynasties.<ref name=\"MRCJune62019\"/>\n\n== Electoral history ==\n{{Election box begin no change\n|title=[[Pasig]] mayoral election, 2019<ref>https://ph.rappler.com/elections/2019/local/region/METRO-MANILA/PASIG-CITY/</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n|party=Aksyon\n|candidate=Vico Sotto\n|votes=209,370\n|percentage=63.27\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|party=Nacionalista Party\n|candidate=Bobby Eusebio\n|votes=121,556\n|percentage=36.73\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n|votes=330,926\n|percentage=100.00%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Philippines}}\n{{Mayors of Metro Manila}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sotto, Vico}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in Metro Manila]]\n[[Category:Filipino Christians]]\n[[Category:Filipino evangelicals]]\n[[Category:Filipino politicians]]\n[[Category:Politics of Pasig]]\n[[Category:People from Pasig]]\n[[Category:Sotto family|Vico]]\n[[Category:Aksyon Demokratiko politicians]]\n[[Category:Ateneo de Manila University alumni]]\n[[Category:Metro Manila city and municipal councilors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Like resume|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Filipino politician}}\n{{Philippine name|Nubla|Sotto}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Vico Sotto\n| image               = Vico Sotto at UA&P CRC meet with Pasig students on June 6 2019.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| caption             = Sotto on October 2019\n| office              = Mayor of [[Pasig]]\n| 1blankname          = Vice Mayor\n| 1namedata           = Iyo Christian C. Bernardo\n| term_start          = June 30, 2019\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = Robert \"Bobby\" Eusebio\n| office1             = Member of the [[Sangguniang Panlungsod]] of [[Pasig]] from the First District\n| term_start1         = June 30, 2016\n| term_end1           = June 30, 2019\n| office2             = Chairman of Public Relations and Information Committee<br />[[Sangguniang Panlungsod]] of [[Pasig]]\n| term_start2         = June 30, 2016\n| term_end2           = June 30, 2019\n| birth_name          = Victor Mar\u00eda Regis Nubla Sotto\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1989|06|17}}\n| birth_place         = [[Pasig]], [[Metro Manila]], Philippines\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = [[Aksyon Demokratiko]]\n| otherparty          = \n| mother              = [[Coney Reyes]]\n| father              = [[Vic Sotto]]\n| spouse              = \n| relations           = [[Oyo Boy Sotto]] <small>(half-brother)</small><br>[[Tito Sotto]] <small>(uncle)</small><br>[[Vicente Sotto]] <small>(great-grandfather)</small><br>[[Pauleen Luna]] <small>(stepmother)</small><br>[[Gian Sotto]] <small>(cousin)</small>\n| profession          = \n| salary              = \n| portfolio           = \n| partner             = \n| children            = \n| alma_mater          = [[Ateneo de Manila University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|AB]], [[Master of Public Administration|MPA]])\n| website             = \n}}\n'''Victor Mar\u00eda Regis''' \"'''Vico'''\" '''Nubla Sotto''' (born June 17, 1989) is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] politician who is the incumbent Mayor of [[Pasig]], Philippines.<ref name=\"millenialmayor\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1135669/millennial-vico-sotto-takes-oath-as-pasig-city-mayor |title=Millennial Vico Sotto takes oath as Pasig City mayor |last=Mercado |first=Neil Arwin |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=July 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701064708/https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1135669/millennial-vico-sotto-takes-oath-as-pasig-city-mayor |archive-date=July 1, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref> Sotto first entered politics when he ran for a seat on the Pasig City Council in 2016. He won the election as an independent, and served a term in the city council.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/04/22/19/vico-sotto |title=Will Vico Sotto be Pasig's final answer? |last=Carpio |first=Audrey |work=ABS CBN News and Public Affairs |access-date=June 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422101627/https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/04/22/19/vico-sotto |archive-date=April 22, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>  He joined the [[Aksyon Demokratiko]] party and ran for Mayor of Pasig in 2019, taking up a platform of [[Participatory democracy|public consultation]], [[Data-driven decision-making|data-driven governance]], [[universal health care]] in Pasig, prioritizing housing programs, easier access to education, and cracking down on [[Corruption in the Philippines|corruption]].<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/> He won the [[2019 Pasig local elections|2019 election]] to earn a six-year mayoral term.<ref name=\"Lalu\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1075306/aksyon-demokratiko-endorses-5-senatorial-bets |title=Aksyon Demokratiko endorses 9 senatorial bets |last=Lalu |first=Gabriel Pabico |access-date=July 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204032445/https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1075306/aksyon-demokratiko-endorses-5-senatorial-bets |archive-date=February 4, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref> \n\nIn March 2020, he received significant public attention<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\">{{Cite news |last=Malasig |first=Jeline |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/03/18/164558/vico-sotto-has-been-stellar-with-his-proactive-covid-19-initiatives-and-filipinos-want-him-to-lead-the-whole-country/ |title=Vico Sotto has been stellar with his proactive COVID-19 initiatives, and Filipinos want him to lead the whole country |date=March 18, 2020 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\"JCRight\"/> due to his leadership of Pasig's quick, data-driven responses to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Metro Manila]], and the resulting [[2020 Luzon enhanced community quarantine]].<ref name=\"JelouEmpathy\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\">{{Cite news |last=Abellon |first=Bam |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/03/20/20/heres-everything-that-mayor-vico-sotto-has-done-so-far-in-response-to-covid-19 |title=Here\u2019s everything that Mayor Vico Sotto has done so far in response to COVID-19 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320204156/https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/03/20/20/heres-everything-that-mayor-vico-sotto-has-done-so-far-in-response-to-covid-19 |archive-date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nSotto was born on June 17, 1989 to actor-comedian-host [[Vic Sotto]] and actress [[Coney Reyes]].<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>  As the son of two celebrities strongly associated with the noontime variety show ''[[Eat Bulaga!]]'', the public expected that Sotto would make regular appearances on the show. However, he was a shy child who often refused to go onstage; eventually his parents stopped asking him.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/> Sotto attended [[Brent International School]] for most of his grade school and high school.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Libarios |first1=Gabby |title=Vico Sotto: The son also rises |url=https://www.pep.ph/peptionary/146255/vico-sotto-a1294-20190929-lfrm3 |website=Philippine Entertainment Portal |accessdate=March 26, 2020 |date=September 29, 2019}}</ref> He graduated from the [[Ateneo de Manila University]] in 2011 with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree in [[political science]]. Sotto would eventually pursue a career in politics, furthering his mastery by pursuing a post-graduate degree in [[public administration]] at the [[Ateneo School of Government]], where he graduated in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sabillo |first1=Kristine |title=Change in Pasig: How Vico Sotto toppled a dynasty |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/05/22/19/change-in-pasig-how-vico-sotto-toppled-a-dynasty |accessdate=May 22, 2019 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Pasig City Council ==\nSotto became a member of [[Sangguniang Panlungsod]] (City Council) of Pasig in 2016,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/breaking-news/2018/07/10/130366/i-am-not-your-father-pasig-city-councilor-vico-sotto-clarifies-dad-tag-of-newspaper/ |title='I am not your father': Pasig City councilor Vico Sotto clarifies 'dad' tag of newspaper - Interaksyon |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |date=October 15, 2018 |work=interaksyon.com |access-date=July 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181015072016/http://www.interaksyon.com/breaking-news/2018/07/10/130366/i-am-not-your-father-pasig-city-councilor-vico-sotto-clarifies-dad-tag-of-newspaper/ |archive-date=October 15, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> serving a single term<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/> which ended when he was sworn in as Mayor on June 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web \n|url= https://www.pep.ph/news/107205/strongpep-special-reportstrong-how-did-showbiz-clans-fare-in-eleksyon2016\n|title= PEP SPECIAL REPORT. How did showbiz clans fare in #Eleksyon2016?\n|last1=\n|first1= \n|date= May 11, 2016\n|publisher= [[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]\n|access-date= May 18, 2019\n}}</ref> \n\nAs an independent Councilor, Sotto faced stiff opposition to his initiatives, making it difficult for him to introduce legislation.  As a result, he was forced to strategize, sacrificing some of the measures{{which|date=April 2020}} he wanted to pass in favor of those he thought most important{{which|date=April 2020}}.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/>\n\nHe focused his attention on the \u201cThe Pasig Transparency Mechanism Ordinance,\u201d which seeks the disclosure of public records, including financial documents and contracts, upon request by ordinary citizens.<ref name=\"AudreyApril222019\"/> Upon its passage, it became the first-ever localized version of the [[Freedom of Information Order (Philippines)|freedom of information law]] in [[Metro Manila]].<ref>{{cite web \n|url= https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1040986/pasig-passes-own-version-of-foi-bill\n|title= Pasig passes own version of FOI bill\n|last1= Enano\n|first1= Jhesset\n|date= October 10, 2018\n|publisher= [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]\n|access-date= May 18, 2019\n}}</ref>\n\n== Pasig Mayor ==\n[[File:Vico_Sotto_at_UA&P_CRC_meet_with_Pasig_students_on_June_6_2019.jpg|thumb|right|Mayor Vico Sotto speaking before Pasig City High School students at the [[University of Asia and the Pacific]], June 6, 2019]]\n{{Recentism|section=yes|date=April 2020}}\n\n=== 2019 campaign ===\nWhen Sotto ran for Mayor in Pasig in 2019, he campaigned on a platform that he called his \u201cBig V\u201d (Big Five) Agenda, saying he planned to focus on universal healthcare, housing programs, education, public consultation, and anti-corruption efforts.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.philstar.com/nation/2019/05/06/1915546/ibanaman-vs-continuity-political-payanig-pasig |title=#IbaNaman vs continuity: Political 'payanig' in Pasig |last=Cabico |first=Gaea Katreena |date=May 6, 2019 |work=The [[Philippine Star]] |access-date=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== 2019 campaign platform ====\n===== Universal health care in Pasig =====\nDuring the campaign, Sotto indicated that his top priority would be healthcare in Pasig, citing it as an important anti-poverty measure. He noted that while there were numerous health facilities such as hospitals in Pasig, it was important that they be properly supplied with medicine.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>\n\n===== Housing programs =====\nAnother priority area Sotto said he would prioritize was housing.  He said he would try to make sure that every family living in Pasig would eventually own their own house.  He also promised that informal settlers would not be forced to leave their homes until primary services and livelihood could be assured at the selected relocation site.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>\n\n===== Education =====\nAs part of his Platform on Education, Sotto pledged to make it easier and cheaper for Pasig residents to qualify for scholarships, removing barriers and reducing requirements in the application process. Among the requirements he singled out for removal was the requirement that parents submit copies of their voter's registration documents while applying for Pasig City scholarships. <ref name=\"metromanila.politics.com.ph\">{{cite web |url=https://metromanila.politics.com.ph/2019/04/14/vico-sotto-wants-to-simplify-scholarship-for-pasig-students-no-more-extra-fees/ |title=Vico Sotto wants to simplify scholarship for Pasig students: No more extra fees! |date=April 14, 2019 |website=Politiko Metro Manila |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417143338/https://metromanila.politics.com.ph/2019/04/14/vico-sotto-wants-to-simplify-scholarship-for-pasig-students-no-more-extra-fees/ |archive-date=April 17, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=July 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Public consultation =====\nIn response to the management style of the previous administration Sotto also promised during the campaign that all city government decisions would go through a public consultation process.  He also promised transparency in government projects, from planning to implementation to monitoring and evaluation.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/> More specific initiatives proposed by Sotto under this agenda item include public officials from appointing members on local special bodies, and forming sectoral councils in areas such as like transport and environmental protection, tasked with developing legislation in those areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1119590/sottos-pledge-i-wont-do-a-eusebio |title=Sotto's pledge: I won't do a Eusebio &#124; Inquirer News |publisher=|date=May 16, 2019 |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Anti-corruption drive =====\nSotto also indicated that his administration's anti-corruption drive would begin with the establishment of a \"Government Efficiency and Anti-Corruption Commission,\" the putting up a Pasig City anti-corruption hotline, and ensuring that a Non-Government Organization or Civil Society Organization would watch over each of the City Government's bidding processes.<ref name=\"GaeaMay62019\"/>\n\n==== Data-driven governance ====\n{{see also|Data-driven decision-making}}\nA key strategy Sotto said he would use in order to achieve his five-point campaign platform was that of [[Data-driven decision-making|data-driven governance]]. On the campaign trail, he said that one of the roots of poor public service in Pasig was the culture of \"palakasan,\" where citizens have to curry the favor of officials in order to get services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/06/30/q-a-with-metro-manila-mayors/ |title=Q & A with Metro Manila mayors: \u00bb Manila Bulletin News |publisher=News.mb.com.ph |date= |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref>  Sotto's proposed solution to this problem was to make sure that decisions on the provision and prioritization of services would be based on data, rather than the political will or whims of officials.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://opinion.inquirer.net/121636/finding-vico |title=Finding Vico &#124; Inquirer Opinion |publisher=Opinion.inquirer.net |date= |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://business.inquirer.net/274577/transforming-metro-manila-cities |title=Transforming Metro Manila cities &#124; Inquirer Business |publisher=|date= |accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019 electoral victory ===\nVico Sotto defeated incumbent mayor Robert Eusebio in the [[2019 Pasig local elections]], ending the 27-year rule of the Eusebio family over the Pasig City Mayoralty.<ref name=\"millenialmayor\"/> He was sworn into office on June 30, 2019.<ref name=\"Rachelle\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.pep.ph/news/144282/pasi-mayor-vico-sotto-funniest-tweets-a716-20190701 |title=Vico Sotto has the funniest tweets after winning as Pasig mayor |last=Siazon |first=Rachelle |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703093135/https://www.pep.ph/news/144282/pasi-mayor-vico-sotto-funniest-tweets-a716-20190701 |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live |publisher=pep.ph}}</ref>\n\n=== Early policies and positions ===\n==== Policy against politicking ====\nSotto received favorable press coverage<ref name=\"tarpaulinABS\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/06/20/19/netizens-laud-vico-sottos-plea-to-have-his-tarpaulin-removed |title=Netizens laud Vico Sotto's plea to have his tarpaulin removed |last=News |first=ABS-CBN |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620092917/https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/06/20/19/netizens-laud-vico-sottos-plea-to-have-his-tarpaulin-removed |archive-date=June 20, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> when he issued a policy statement against the proliferation of political propaganda signages, even before his inauguration.  A supporter had taken the occasion of Sotto's 30th Birthday on July 17 to post a tarpaulin greeting the Mayor-elect on his birthday.  A few days later, Sotto went on Twitter to request that the tarpaulin be removed, and asserting that such politically-oriented signage bearing his image would be discouraged during his term.<ref name=\"InteraksyonTarpaulin\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/06/21/150819/vico-sotto-first-instructions-mayor/ |title=Pasig Mayor-elect Vico Sotto's first instructions before assuming office |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |date=June 21, 2019 |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622150721/http://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/06/21/150819/vico-sotto-first-instructions-mayor/ |archive-date=June 22, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nHe has also made statements discouraging the \"celebrity treatment\" of politicians in the Philippines\n<ref>{{Cite news |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/trends-spotlights/2019/08/26/153962/pasig-city-mayor-vico-sotto-tells-public-stop-viewing-government-officials-celebrities/ |title=Pasig Mayor Vico Sotto wants the public to stop treating government officials as celebrities |date=August 26, 2019 |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828031111/http://www.interaksyon.com/trends-spotlights/2019/08/26/153962/pasig-city-mayor-vico-sotto-tells-public-stop-viewing-government-officials-celebrities/ |archive-date=August 28, 2019 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==== Reassessment of traffic management ====\nSotto's first executive order upon being sworn in as Mayor put in place a Pasig City Traffic Management Task Force, which was tasked to \"review and propose new solutions for the current mobility and traffic situation\" within 45 days.<ref name=\"Drei\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/mayor-vico-sotto-pasig-coding-a962-20190701 |title=Mayor Vico Sotto's first executive order suspends odd-even coding |last=Laurel |first=Drei |work=Top Gear Magazine |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703093727/https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/mayor-vico-sotto-pasig-coding-a962-20190701 |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref>  The same executive order abolished the Pasig City odd-even coding scheme which the previous administration had implemented on top of the [[Metro Manila Development Authority]]'s [[Unified Vehicular Volume Reduction Program|Traffic Coding Scheme]] - a double burden which Sotto had earlier decried as being \"disjointed and unjust.\"<ref name=\"Drei\"/>\n\n==== Zagu Foods picketline incident ====\nOn July 9, 2019, media reports noted that Sotto had visited protesters who were being forced away from their picket line in front of the main factory of Zagu Foods Corporation in Pasig.  He reminded Zagu Foods' management that the protesters were within their rights to engage in protest activities.<ref name=\"Consuelo\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1139740/vico-sotto-to-zagu-management-respect-workers-right-to-picket |title=Vico Sotto to Zagu management: Respect workers' right to picket |last=Marquez |first=Consuelo |date=July 9, 2019 |work=The [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=July 10, 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"CatalinaRicciRegencyZagu\">{{Cite news |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/11/18/157591/pasig-mayor-vico-sotto-took-side-constituents-against-companies-twice/ |title=The two instances when Pasig Mayor Vico Sotto took the side of his constituents against big companies |date=November 18, 2019 |work=interaksyon |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119130202/http://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2019/11/18/157591/pasig-mayor-vico-sotto-took-side-constituents-against-companies-twice/ |archive-date=November 19, 2019 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==== Regent Foods picketline incident ====\nIn November 2019, Sotto intervened in another picketline incident - this time with Regent Foods Corporation, 23 of whose workers were arrested after they clashed with company security guards and police officers while protesting the company's labor practices.  Sotto called on Regency to \"rethink on the charges it filed against its employees,\" issuing a statement saying that \u201cThese people are not criminals; they do not have the goal of hurting you. They are fighting for what they believe to be just.\u201d  Sotto also said he was raising funds for the bail money which the 23 arrested employees would need.<ref name=\"CatalinaRicciRegencyZagu\"/>\n\n==== Crackdown on illegal POGO-related services ====\nIn February 2020, Sotto again gained positive media reactions as a result of his efforts to crack down on illegally-operating businesses linked to Philippine Offshore Gaming Operators (POGOs).  On February 23, Sotto ordered the closure Fu Yuan Ji, a restaurant catering to POGO employees which had opened without getting a permit to operate from the city.<ref name=\"CatalinaRicciPOGOs\">{{Cite news |last=Malasig |first=Jeline |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/02/24/162814/vico-sotto-pasig-city-crackdown-pogos-chinese-restaurant/ |title=Vico Sotto gives teeth to city laws vs unregistered Chinese resto |date=February 24, 2020 |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225074628/https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/02/24/162814/vico-sotto-pasig-city-crackdown-pogos-chinese-restaurant/ |archive-date=February 25, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== COVID-19 crisis response ===\nSotto received significant positive attention in both traditional and social media in response to Pasig's quick, data-driven responses to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Metro Manila]], and the resulting [[2020 Luzon enhanced community quarantine]] beginnning March 17, 2020.<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"JCRight\">{{Cite news |last=Gotinga |first=J. C. |url=http://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/inside-track/255321-vico-sotto-says-always-do-what-believe-is-right |title=Vico Sotto: I will always just do what I believe is right |date=March 21, 2020 |work=[[Rappler]] |access-date=March 21, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321162851/https://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/inside-track/255321-vico-sotto-says-always-do-what-believe-is-right |archive-date=March 21, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"JelouEmpathy\">{{Cite magazine |last=Galang |first=Jelou |date=March 20, 2020 |title=Empathy with action is Mayor Vico Sotto's winning combo |url=https://www.scoutmag.ph/featured/empathy-with-action-mayor-vico-sotto-jeloug-20200320 |url-status=live |magazine=Scout Magazine |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163418/https://www.scoutmag.ph/featured/empathy-with-action-mayor-vico-sotto-jeloug-20200320 |archive-date=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Before the Luzon quarantine ====\nNational media outlets<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"JCRight\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\"/> noted that even before the national government implemented a community quarantine in the Metro Manila area, Sotto\u2019s administration prepared for the coming of COVID-19 by:\n* asking experts to brief Pasig\u2019s health workers about COVID-19 cases;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* establishing and training COVID-19 response teams;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* Providing a total of more than 1,000 sets of disinfecting kits to all of the Pasig\u2019s barangays;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/> and\n* Disinfecting public places \u2013 from the public market and public schools to even streets and sidewalks, as well as Pasig City Hall.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* Sotto himself spoke with the management with Pasig city\u2019s private hospitals to make sure they are ready to take on COVID-19 patients.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* Sotto also kept Pasig constituents constantly informed about necessary precautions and updated about the situation through his official social media accounts.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n\n==== During the Luzon quarantine ====\nAccounts<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"JCRight\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\"/> also noted that once the enhanced quarantine was put in place on March 17, the Sotto administration:\n* Placed the city government on skeleton staff, in keeping with national policy, rearranging schedules so frontline government services could be sustained;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* ensured the full salaries for all city government employees;<ref name=\"ABSCBNPasigSalariesCOVID\">{{Cite news |last=News |first=ABS-CBN |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/18/20/all-pasig-employees-to-get-full-pay-during-covid-19-quarantine-vico-sotto |title=All Pasig employees to get full pay during COVID-19 quarantine: Vico Sotto |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Gotinga |first=J. C. |url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/254893-vico-sotto-vows-full-salaries-pasig-government-workers-coronavirus-lockdown |title=Vico Sotto vows full salaries for all Pasig government workers during lockdown |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* implemented a nightly 8 pm to 5 am curfew;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n* put up rules penalizing hoarders of essential goods;<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/> \n* continued disinfecting operations in public places,<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/> and procured disinfectant drones so that hard-to-reach areas could be disinfected;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/vico-sotto-disinfectant-drones-src-esquireph-a4349-20200318 |title=Pasig City procures disinfectant drones to fight COVID-19 |work=Top Gear Philippines |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"ABSCBNDronesMotelsCOVID\"/>\n* established sanitation tents at the Pasig city hall, Pasig City General Hospital (PCGH), and the Pasig City Children\u2019s Hospital (Child\u2019s Hope);<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/><ref name=\"SanitationTentsLook\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/18/20/look-sanitation-tents-installed-in-pasig-city-hall-public-hospitals |title=LOOK: Sanitation tents installed in Pasig City hall, public hospitals |work=ABS CBN News and Public Affairs |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* distributed food packs and bottles of vitamins to Pasig residents;<ref name=\"JCRight\"/> and \n* arranged for the conversion of some of Pasig\u2019s motels as quarantine facilities COVID-19 patients.<ref name=\"ABSCBNDronesMotelsCOVID\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/19/20/pasig-buys-disinfection-drones-turns-motels-to-quarantine-and-staff-lodging-vico-sotto |title=Pasig buys disinfection drones, turns motels to quarantine and staff lodging: Vico Sotto |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* Sotto himself regularly inspected the checkpoints to make sure procedures were being followed and the rights of citizens respected despite the curfew.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/><ref name=\"Abellon\"/>\n* Sotto also met the appropriate teams from The Medical City, PCGH, Child\u2019s Hope, and the City Health Office, ensuring proper coordination and the exchange of good practices in pandemic response.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n\n==== Transportation initiatives during the Luzon quarantine ====\nSotto's administration also executed a number of transportation initiatives during the enhanced community quarantine.  Most of these were generally praised, including the deployment of Pasig city\u2019s fleet of buses to service essential workers, and the lending of \u201cPasig Bike Share\u201d bicycle units to health workers and other frontline personnel.<ref name=\"JCRight\"/>\n\nOne initiative that was questioned during the early days of the quarantine, however, was that Pasig initially allowed limited tricycle trips for people with legitimate reasons to commute, such as chemotherapy and other health issues.<ref name=\"Jeline_Malasig-Sotto\"/>  This was done on the basis of Pasig city risk analysis which determined that more residents would die if they were deprived of transport services.<ref name=\"AllysaRisk\">{{Cite news |last=Nievera |first=Allysa |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/18/mayor-sotto-says-total-ban-on-tricycles-in-pasig-adds-risk-to-health-situation/ |title=Mayor Sotto says total ban on tricycles in Pasig adds risk to health situation  |date=March 18, 2020}}</ref>  Sotto thus went on national media pleading to the national governement that an exception be made for Pasig's tricycles, based on the studies.<ref name=\"JCUrge\">{{Cite news |last=Gotinga |first=J. C. |url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/254986-vico-sotto-urges-national-government-allow-tricycles-coronavirus-lockdown |title=Vico Sotto urges nat'l gov't to allow tricycles during coronavirus lockdown |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> However, on March 19, 2020 the national government informed Sotto that they insisted all forms of public transport, including tricycles, would be banned.  Sotto immediately responded that Pasig would stop allowing Tricycles to ply their routes.<ref name=\"PasigTricycleCompliance\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/metro/730479/vico-sotto-pasig-to-follow-nat-l-gov-t-on-tricycles-ban/story/ |title=Vico Sotto: Pasig to follow nat\u2019l gov\u2019t on tricycles ban |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nIn response to media coverage of this, private companies began donating vehicles such as Community Managed Electric Transport (COMET) bus units to augment Pasig city's fleet of free rides that can be offered to the public.<ref name=\"PasigCOMETs\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.wheninmanila.com/tricycles-not-allowed-pasig-gets-creative-by-deploying-these-electric-vehicles/ |title=Tricycles not allowed, Pasig gets creative by deploying these electric vehicles |date=March 20, 2020 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en-US}}</ref>  The city was eventualy able to acquire e-tricycles which were specifically assigned to provide free transportation for Pasig City residents who had health and hospitalization needs such as dialysis or chemotherapy<ref name=\"DreiETrykes\">{{Cite news |last=Laurel |first=Drei |url=https://www.topgear.com.ph/news/motoring-news/pasig-city-free-transport-dialysis-chemotherapy-a962-20200330 |title=Pasig City offers free transport for those in need of dialysis, chemotherapy |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> - the residents which the risk assessment determined would be endangered by the ban on tricycles.<ref name=\"AllysaRisk\"/><ref name=\"VicoUmapela\">{{Cite news |last=Canoy |first=Jeff |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/video/news/03/18/20/vico-sotto-umapelang-payagang-bumiyahe-ang-tricycle-drivers-sa-pasig |title=Vico Sotto umapelang payagang bumiyahe ang tricycle drivers sa Pasig |date=March 18, 2020 |work=ABS CBN News and Public Affairs |access-date=April 1, 2020 |language=tl}}</ref>\n\n===== Tricycle operations controversy =====\n\nOn March 24, the Philippine legislature passed the [[Bayanihan to Heal as One Act]] which gave national government additional powers to combat the pandemic.<ref name=\"CatalinaRicciOne\">{{Cite news |last=Madarang |first=Catalina Ricci S. |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/03/26/164950/bayanihan-to-heal-as-one-act-whats-at-stake-law/ |title=The 'Bayanihan to Heal as One Act' and what's at stake in the law |date=March 26, 2020 |access-date=April 1, 2020 |work=InterAksyon |language=en-US}}</ref> The [[National Bureau of Investigation (Philippines)|National Bureau of Investigation]] (NBI) invoked the said law on April 1 against Sotto, summoning him to appear at their office on April 7, claiming that he had violated the law's provision which bans public transportation. Sotto responded by saying that he had complied with the national government's order to stop tricycle operations [[Ex post facto law|prior to the enactment of the law]] on March 25. Senate President [[Tito Sotto]], an uncle of the mayor and a principal author of the law in question, supported his claim.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/256687-senators-reaction-nbi-summon-vico-sotto-coronavirus-lockdown|title=Tito Sotto 'defends' Vico: 'Violation of Bayanihan law can't be retroactive'|last=Rey|first=Aika|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> Vice President [[Leni Robredo]] and Senator [[Francis Pangilinan]] were some of the other politicians who questioned the NBI's actions, stating the unconstitutionality of criminalizing an act committed retroactively.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/4/1/nbi-vico-sotto-luzon-quarantine.html|title=NBI asks Vico Sotto to explain 'violation' of quarantine policy|work=CNN Philippines|language=en|access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> Social media responded heavily with criticism towards the NBI for allegedly singling out the mayor, with the [[hashtag]] \"#ProtectVico\" trended on [[Twitter]] worldwide that day.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vico Sotto 'confident nothing will happen' in NBI probe |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/video/news/04/05/20/vico-sotto-confident-nothing-will-happen-in-nbi-probe |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Political affiliation ==\nSotto originally ran for a seat in the Pasig Sanguniang Panglungsod as an independent, and won a seat without having any party affiliation.  \n\nIn 2019, Sotto was sworn in as a member of [[Aksyon Demokratiko]], a national political party founded by former Senator [[Raul Roco]] in 1997. He was sworn into the party alongside [[Roman Romulo]], who would also win as representative in Pasig City's sole legislative district; and Marielle del Rosario, who likewise ran as representative of [[Navotas City]].<ref name=\"Lalu\"/>  Sotto has refused to join bigger, more-established parties despite political pressure to do so,<ref name=\"MRCJune62019\">{{Cite news |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1121807/vico-sotto-we-need-to-go-beyond-yellow-vs-dds |title=Vico Sotto: We need to go beyond yellow vs DDS |last=Reysio-Cruz |first=Matthew |date=June 3, 2019 |work=The [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=June 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521224751/https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1121807/vico-sotto-we-need-to-go-beyond-yellow-vs-dds |archive-date=May 21, 2019 |url-status=live |language=en}}</ref> explaining that he chose to join the party because he shared its platform of pushing for Freedom of Information, political party reform, and the end of political dynasties.<ref name=\"MRCJune62019\"/>\n\n== Electoral history ==\n{{Election box begin no change\n|title=[[Pasig]] mayoral election, 2019<ref>https://ph.rappler.com/elections/2019/local/region/METRO-MANILA/PASIG-CITY/</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n|party=Aksyon\n|candidate=Vico Sotto\n|votes=209,370\n|percentage=63.27\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|party=Nacionalista Party\n|candidate=Bobby Eusebio\n|votes=121,556\n|percentage=36.73\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n|votes=330,926\n|percentage=100.00%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Philippines}}\n{{Mayors of Metro Manila}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sotto, Vico}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in Metro Manila]]\n[[Category:Filipino Christians]]\n[[Category:Filipino evangelicals]]\n[[Category:Filipino politicians]]\n[[Category:Politics of Pasig]]\n[[Category:People from Pasig]]\n[[Category:Sotto family|Vico]]\n[[Category:Aksyon Demokratiko politicians]]\n[[Category:Ateneo de Manila University alumni]]\n[[Category:Metro Manila city and municipal councilors]]\n", "name_user": "PatTag2659", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTricycle operations controversy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vico_Sotto"}
{"title_page": "National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic", "text_new": "{{Short description|Internal responses of the nations of the world.}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic sidebar|expanded=issues}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] spread to many countries around the world, with the most affected countries being the United States, Italy, Spain, China, France, Iran, Switzerland and South Korea.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Guti\u00e9rrez |first1=Pablo |title=Coronavirus map: how Covid-19 is spreading across the world |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/ng-interactive/2020/mar/24/coronavirus-map-how-covid-19-is-spreading-across-the-world |work=The Guardian}}</ref> National response measures have been varied, and have included containment measures such as lockdowns, quarantines, and curfews. This is a dynamic list of different responses by various nations across the world.<ref name=\"WOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/|title=Coronavirus Update (Live) \u2013 Worldometer|website=worldometers.info}}</ref>\n[[File:Tree- How Covid-19 spreads.png|thumb|right|upright=1.63]]\n\n== China ==\n{{Main|2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China}}\n{{2020 coronavirus quarantines}}{{-}}\n[[File:Staff monitoring passengers' body temperature in Wuhan railway station during the Wuhan coronavirus outbreak.jpg|thumb|Infrared cameras were installed in [[Wuhan railway station]] to check passengers' body temperature before they board the trains.|link=Special:FilePath/Staff_monitoring_passengers'_body_temperature_in_Wuhan_railway_station_during_the_Wuhan_coronavirus_pandemic.jpg]]\n[[File:\u822a\u62cd\u6b66\u6c49\u4e2d\u5fc3\u57ce\u533a\u673a\u52a8\u8f66\u7981\u884c\u540e\u9053\u8def\uff1a\u5c11\u6709\u8f66\u8f86\u8e2a\u5f71-Wg-8rMZAsY0.webm|thumb|right|'Aerial photography of roads after motor vehicles are banned in central urban areas of Wuhan: few vehicle traces' \u2013 Video news from [[China News Service]]]]\n[[File:Changchun Longjia Airport Terminal 2 Security Check (20200126) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|Masked passengers undergoing temperature checks at [[Changchun Longjia International Airport|Changchun Longjia Airport]] in northeast China]]\n[[File:West Kowloon Station queue 20200125.jpg|thumb|right|Hong Kong residents queueing to refund their [[Hong Kong Express Rail Link|bullet train]] tickets to the mainland in [[West Kowloon railway station]]]]\nThe first person known to have fallen ill due to the new virus was in Wuhan on 1 December 2019.<ref name=\"AutoDW-67\"/> A public notice on the outbreak was released by Wuhan health authority on 31 December; the initial notice informed Wuhan residents that there was no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission of the virus, that the disease is preventable and controllable, and that people can wear masks when going out.<ref name=\"AutoDW-68\"/> WHO was informed of the outbreak on the same day.<ref name=\"AutoDW-69\"/>\n\nOn 7 January 2020, the Chinese [[Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China|Communist Party Politburo Standing Committee]] discussed novel coronavirus prevention and control.<ref name=\"Xi's meeting\"/><ref name=\"Xi's meeting 2\"/>\n\nOn 20 January, [[Zhong Nanshan]], a scientist at China's [[National Health Commission]] who played a prominent role in the SARS epidemic, declared its potential for human-to-human transmission, after two cases emerged in [[Guangdong]] of infection by family members who had visited Wuhan.<ref name=\"AutoDW-70\"/> This was later confirmed by the Wuhan government, which announced a number of new measures such as cancelling the [[Chinese New Year]] celebrations, in addition to measures such as checking the temperature of passengers at transport terminals first introduced on 14 January.<ref name=\"AutoDW-71\"/> A [[2020 Hubei lockdowns|quarantine]] was announced on 23 January 2020 stopping travel in and out of Wuhan.<ref name=\"channelnewsasia12306684\"/>\n\nOn 25 January, Chinese authorities banned the use of private vehicles in [[Wuhan]]. Only vehicles that are transporting critical supplies or emergency response vehicles are allowed to move within the city.<ref name=\"abc11902006\"/>\n\nOn 26 January, a leading group tasked with the prevention and control of the novel coronavirus pandemic was established, led by [[Premier of the People's Republic of China|Chinese Premier]] [[Li Keqiang]].<ref name=\"Premier leading\"/><ref name=\"Premier visiting\"/> The leading group decided to extend the Spring Festival [[Golden Week (China)|holiday]] to contain the outbreak.<ref name=\"AutoDW-72\"/>\n\nChina Customs started requiring that all passengers entering and exiting China fill in an extra health declaration form from 26 January. The health declaration form was mentioned in China's Frontier Health and Quarantine Law, granting the customs rights to require it if needed.<ref name=\"AutoDW-73\"/><ref name=\"xinhuanet1125502381\"/><ref name=\"20200126cgtn\"/>\n\nOn 27 January, the [[General Office of the State Council]] of China, one of the top governing bodies of the People's Republic, officially declared a nation-wide extension on the New Year holiday and the postponement of the coming spring semester. The office extended the previously scheduled [[Public holidays in China|public holiday]] from 30 January, to 2 February, while it said school openings for the spring semester would be announced in the future.<ref name=\"xinhuanet138735904\"/> Some universities with open campuses also banned the public from visiting.<ref name=\"bjnews678863\"/> On 23 January, the education department in [[Hunan]], which neighbours the centre of the outbreak Hubei province, stated it would strictly ban off-school tutors and restrict student gatherings.<ref name=\"xinhuanet1125498917\"/> Education departments in Shanghai and Shenzhen also imposed bans on off-school tutoring and requested that schools track and report students who had been to Wuhan or Hubei province during the winter break.<ref name=\"xinhuanet138732282\"/><ref name=\"people33743688\"/> The semi-autonomous regions of Hong Kong and [[Macau]] also announced adjustments on schooling schedules. Hong Kong's [[Chief Executive of Hong Kong|Chief Executive]] [[Carrie Lam]] declared an emergency at a press conference on 25 January, saying [[Government of Hong Kong|the government]] would close primary and secondary schools for two more weeks on top of the previously scheduled New Year holiday, pushing the date for school reopening to 17 February.<ref name=\"scmp3047645\"/><ref name=\"apnews-b2810ce\"/> Macau closed several museums and libraries, and prolonged the New Year holiday break to 11 February for higher education institutions and 10 February for others.<ref name=\"xinhuanet1125500373\"/> The [[University of Macau]] said they would track the physical conditions of students who have been to Wuhan during the New Year break.<ref name=\"AutoDW-74\"/>\n\nAfter the Chinese New Year on 25 January, there would be another peak of people travelling back from their home towns to workplaces as a part of Chunyun. Several provinces and cities encouraged people to stay in their hometowns and not travel back. Eastern China's [[Suzhou]] also encouraged [[Telecommuting|remote working]] via the Internet and further prolonged the spring festival break.<ref name=\"CaixinJan26QianTong\"/>\n\nThe [[Civil Aviation Administration of China]] and the [[China Railway|China State Railway Group]], which regulate China's civil aviation and operates rail services, announced on 24 January that passengers could have full refunds for their plane and train tickets without any surcharges, regardless of whether their flight or train will go through Wuhan or not.<ref name=\"20200124reuters-refunds\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-75\"/> [[Ministry of Culture and Tourism of the People's Republic of China|China's Ministry of Culture and Tourism]] ordered travel agencies and online tourism firms to suspend [[package tour]]s and stop offering \"flight+hotel\" bundles.<ref name=\"CaixinJan26QianTong\" /><ref name=\"20200124bloomberg\"/>\n\nAdditional provinces and cities outside Hubei imposed travel restrictions. Beijing suspended all [[intercity bus service]]s on 25 January,<ref name=\"chinadaily310128217273397\"/> with several others following suit.<ref name=\"CaixinJan26QianTong\" />\n\n[[File:A Screen Display During Wuhan Coronavirus Outbreak.jpg|thumb|right|A screen display in [[Hefei]] showing \"early detection, early reporting, early quarantine, early diagnosis, early treatment\" during the coronavirus pandemic|link=Special:FilePath/A_Screen_Display_During_Wuhan_coronavirus_pandemic.jpg]]\nOn 1 February 2020, Xinhua News reported that China's [[Supreme People's Procuratorate]] (SPP) has \"asked procuratorates nationwide to fully play their role to create a favourable judicial environment in the fight against the novel coronavirus pandemic.\" This includes severe punishments for those found guilty of dereliction of duty and the withholding of information for officials. Tougher charges were proscribed for commercial criminal activities such as \"the pushing up of prices, profiteering and severely disturbing market order\" along with the \"production and sale of fake and shoddy protective equipment and medicines.\" Prosecuting actions against patients who deliberately spread the infection or refuse examination or compulsory isolation along with threats of violence against medical personnel were also urged. The statement also included urging to prosecute those found \"fabricating coronavirus-related information that may lead to panic among the public, making up and spreading rumours about the virus, sabotaging the implementation of the law and endangering public security\" and also stressed \"harshly punishing the illegal hunting of wildlife under state protection, as well as improving inspection and quarantine measures for fresh food and meat products.\"<ref name=\"xinhuanet138747853\"/>\n\nMuseums throughout China are temporarily closed.<ref name=\":12\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-76\"/> The National Cultural Heritage Administration (NCHA) asked museums around the country to move their exhibits and galleries temporarily online<ref name=\"AutoDW-77\"/> via a program that the NCHA is launching.<ref name=\":12\" /><ref name=\":13\"/>\n\n==== Quarantine ====\n\n{{Main|2020 Hubei lockdowns}}\nOn 23 January 2020, a [[quarantine]] on [[lockdown|travel in and out]] of Wuhan was imposed in an effort to stop the spread of the virus out of Wuhan. Flights, trains, public buses, the metro system, and long-distance coaches were suspended indefinitely. Large-scale gatherings and group tours were also suspended.<ref name=\"channelnewsasia12306684\" /> By 24 January 2020, a total of 15 cities in Hubei, including Wuhan, were placed under similar quarantine measures.<ref name=\":0\"/> On 27 and 28 January 2020, [[Xiangyang]] closed its railway stations and suspended all ferry operations, after shutting down its airport and intercity bus services earlier. Thus, the entire Hubei province entered a city-by-city quarantine, save for the [[Shennongjia]] Forestry District.{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\nBefore the quarantine began, some in Wuhan questioned the reliability of the figures from the Chinese government as well as the government response, with some calling for quarantine,<ref name=\"bbc51205074\"/> and a post also showed sick people and three dead bodies covered in white sheets on the floor of a hospital on 24 January, although many such posts in Weibo about the epidemic have since been deleted.<ref name=\"20200128nytimes\"/><ref name=\"20200126telegraph\"/>\n\nDue to quarantine measures, Wuhan residents rushed to stockpile essential goods, food, and fuel; prices rose significantly.<ref name=\"20200123reuters\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-78\"/> 5,000,000 people left Wuhan, with 9,000,000 left in the city.<ref name=\"abc11902378\"/>\n\nOn 26 January, the city of [[Shantou]] in Guangdong declared a partial lockdown,<ref name=\"AutoDW-79\"/> though this was reversed two hours later.<ref name=\"20200126reuters\"/> Residents had rushed to supermarkets to stock food as soon as the lockdown was declared, until the authorities reversed their decision. ''[[Caixin]]'' said, that the wording of Shantou's initial declaration was \"unprecedentedly strict\" and will severely affect residents' lives, if implemented as-is. Shantou's Department for Outbreak Control later clarified that it would not restrict travelling, but would sterilise vehicles used for transportation.<ref name=\"caixin101508610\"/>\n\n<!-- \"Expressway\" and \"highway\" are official terms that should NOT be changed into corresponding British English wordings. \u2022 Beijing's underground transport is called a \"subway,\"\n while ALL other Chinese cities' underground transport is called \"metro\". -->Local authorities in Beijing and several other major cities, including [[Hangzhou]], [[Guangzhou]], Shanghai, and [[Shenzhen]], announced on 26 January, that these cities will not impose a lockdown similar to those in Hubei province. Rumours of these potential lockdowns had spread widely prior to the official announcements.<ref name=\"bjnews680010\"/> A spokesperson of Beijing's Municipal Transportation Commission claimed that the [[Expressways of China|expressways]], [[China National Highways|highways]], [[Beijing subway|subways]], and buses were operating normally. To ease the residents' panic, the Hangzhou city government stressed that the city would not be locked down from the outside world, and both cities said that they would introduce precautions against potential risks.<ref name=\"chinadaily310128217273520\"/>\n\nOn 2 February 2020, the city of [[Wenzhou]] in Zhejiang also implemented a partial lockdown, closing 46 of the 54 highway checkpoints.<ref name=\"20200202wenzhou\"/>\n\nOn 4 February 2020, two more cities in Zhejiang province restricted the movement of residents. The city of [[Taizhou, Zhejiang|Taizhou]], three Hangzhou districts, and some in [[Ningbo]] began to only allow one person per household to go outside every two days to buy necessities, city officials said. More than 12 million people are affected by the new restrictions.<ref name=\"ChannelNewsAsia\"/>\n\nBy 6 February 2020, a total of four Zhejiang cities\u2014Wenzhou, Hangzhou, Ningbo, and Taizhou\u2014were under the \"passport\" system, allowing only one person per household to leave their home every two days. These restrictions apply to over 30&nbsp;million people.<ref name=\"SCMP 20200206\" />\n\nOutside mainland China, some [[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships|cruise ships]] were quarantined after passengers developed symptoms or tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. The ''[[Costa Smeralda (ship)|Costa Smeralda]]'' was quarantined on 30 January off [[Civitavecchia]] in Italy, after passengers developed flu-like symptoms \u2013 the quarantine was lifted when tests for the virus came back negative.<ref name=\"AutoDW-80\"/> Two further ships were quarantined on 5 February: ''[[Diamond Princess (ship)|Diamond Princess]]'' in the [[Port of Yokohama]], Japan and ''[[World Dream]]'', which returned to Hong Kong after being refused entry to [[Kaohsiung]], Taiwan. In both cases, passengers and crew tested positive.<ref name=\"AutoDW-81\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-86\" /<ref name=\"cnbcWD\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-82\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-83\"/> On 10 February passengers were allowed to disembark the ''World Dream'' \"without the need to self-quarantine after leaving.\"<ref name=\"AutoDW-84\"/>\n\nThe ''Diamond Princess'' was completely disembarked by 1 March, with countries imposing various quarantines for citizens they evacuated.<ref name=\"AutoDW-85\" />> <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51555420|title=Growing criticism over Japan cruise quarantine|date=2020-02-20|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-26|language=en-GB}}</ref> As of 26 March, 712 people from the ship have been diagnosed and 10 have died.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/|title=Coronavirus Update (Live): 520,395 Cases and 23,593 Deaths from COVID-19 Virus Outbreak - Worldometer|website=www.worldometers.info|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\nAlthough not quarantined {{MS|Westerdam}} has been [[MS Westerdam#2019-20 coronavirus|refused entry]] by several ports after departing Hong Kong on 1 February.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: 'Pariah' cruise ship rejected by five ports docks at last |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51484625 |publisher=BBC News |date=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"150px\">\nFile:Citizens of Wuhan lining up outside of a drug store to buy masks during the Wuhan coronavirus outbreak.jpg|People queueing outside a Wuhan pharmacy to buy face masks and medical supplies\nFile:Wuhan citizens rush to buy vegetables during Wuhan coronavirus outbreak.jpg|Residents of Wuhan wearing masks rushed out to nearby markets to buy vegetables and other food on 23 January during the outbreak\nFile:Last train of Wuhan metro before authorities lock down the city for the Wuhan coronavirus outbreak.jpg|Residents of Wuhan waiting for the last train of the city's metro on 10&nbsp;am, 22 January\n</gallery>\n\n==== Outdoor restrictions ====\nOn 1 February, [[Huanggang]], Hubei implemented a measure whereby only one person from each household is permitted to go outside for provisions once every two days, except for medical reasons or to work at shops or pharmacies.<ref name=\":20\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed sortable\" style=\"text-align:right;\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" |<u>'''Administrative divisions with family outdoor restrictions'''</u>\n!Administrative<br />division\n!Division<br />type\n!Provincial<br />division\n!Start date\n!End date\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" |Ordinary<br />population\n!Population<br />year\n!Notes\n|-\n|[[Huanggang]]<ref name=\":20\" />\n|City\n|Hubei\n|2020-02-01\n|\n|6,162,069\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Wenzhou]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-87\"/>\n|City\n|Zhejiang\n|2020-02-02\n|2020-02-08\n|9,190,000\n|2017\n|\n|-\n|[[Wenling]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-88\"/>\n|City\n|Zhejiang\n|2020-02-02\n|\n|1,366,800\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Fangchenggang]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-89\"/>\n|City\n|Guangxi\n|2020-02-02\n|2020-02-08\n|860,100\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Guigang]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-90\"/>\n|City\n|Guangxi\n|2020-02-02\n|\n|1,562,200<br />(Urban only)\n|2010\n|Urban districts only\n|-\n|[[Yuzhou District|Yuzhou]],<ref name=\"auto6\"/> [[Yulin, Guangxi|Yulin]]\n|District\n|Guangxi\n|2020-02-02\n|2020-02-09\n|900,000\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Zhouzhi County|Zhouzhi]],<ref name=\":19\"/> [[Xi'an]]\n|County\n|Shaanxi\n|2020-02-02\n|\n|562,768\n|2010\n|One person per household every day\n|-\n|[[Huyi District|Huyi]],<ref name=\":19\" /> [[Xi'an]]\n|District\n|Shaanxi\n|2020-02-03\n|2020-02-09\n|556,377\n|2010\n|One person per household every day\n|-\n|[[Bengbu]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-91\"/>\n|City\n|Anhui\n|2020-02-03\n|\n|3,164,467\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Huaibei]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-92\"/>\n|City\n|Anhui\n|2020-02-03\n|\n|2,114,276\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Bincheng District|Bincheng]],<ref name=\"auto6\" /><br />[[Binzhou]]\n|District\n|Shandong\n|2020-02-03\n|2020-02-09\n|682,717\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Taizhou, Zhejiang|Taizhou]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-93\"/>\n|City\n|Zhejiang\n|2020-02-03\n|\n|5,968,838\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Hangzhou]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-94\"/>\n|City\n|Zhejiang\n|2020-02-04\n|\n|9,806,000\n|2017\n|\n|-\n|[[Ezhou]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-95\"/>\n|City\n|Hubei\n|2020-02-04\n|\n|1,048,668\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Fuzhou]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-96\"/>\n|City\n|Fujian\n|2020-02-04\n|\n|7,660,000\n|2017\n|\n|-\n|[[Xuzhou]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-97\"/>\n|City\n|Jiangsu\n|2020-02-04\n|2020-02-08\n|8,577,225\n|2010\n|\n|-\n|[[Jingdezhen]]<ref name=\"AutoDW-98\"/>\n|City\n|Jiangxi\n|2020-